node.text:
It's incredible how just a few words can light that fire inside of us and give us strength to go through the storm. I believe it brings up the power that is already within.

And it really came in the right timing in my life. Thank you @jesperwestmark for that 🙏🏻❤

node.text:
A song for the Earth ❤🌿

"The earth does not belong to man, man belongs to the earth.
All things are connected like the blood that unites us all. Man did not weave the web of life, he is merely a strand in it. 
Whatever he does to the web, he does to himself" - Chief Seattle

#kulning #herdingcall #music #earth #nordicmusic

node.text:
Tomorrow is the very last day of the summer before the first month of autumn begins. But I know summer always keep some goodies for September. I actually enjoy September more than July and August.
The temperature, the light, the freshness, the cold swims, the misty mornings...we got all the best ahead of us 😍🙏🏻

#lastofsummer #august #sweden

node.text:
I went down to the lake this Friday evening. It was the first calm and warm evening in a long time and the lake was like a mirror. The quietness of the late summer is so special. The cycle of life is heading towards rest now. 

I did some whisteling (or I don't really know what to call it?) because it was so quiet and no wind so the echoes was breathtaking! 
Sometimes the echoes travel many times...hmm how to describe it...the echo makes a echo of the echo 😜
So its repeating itself and that always sounds as if someone is answering me with the same voice as I, since it comes many seconds later after the first echoe.

That sound is hard to capture on camera but I will definitely try to capture it with my soundrecorder one day.

Have a beautiful weekend everyone ❤🥰😘

#whisteling #echo #sound #sweden

node.text:
Happy 11th Birthday Nanook! ❤🥳 I love you with all my heart, my best friend and fellow companion. You've been there for me my whole adult life and there is just no words to describe how grateful I am for sharing these 11 years with you. 

Today we celebrated his Birthday with his new found friend Harry (my parents puppy) and my heart melted a thousand times watching them together ❤
Im sure they will become really good friends. 

#nanook #dog #puppy #goldenretriever #labrador #dogbirthday

node.text:
The love I feel for this land and the beautiful nature all around me is my greatest source to joy and creativity. It's part of every song, film, photo and painting I've ever made. 
Feeling so deeply grateful that I get to breathe this fresh forest air every day and  use the energy from it to continue creating and sharing a piece of my little world with all of you ❤

Did you know that my music will soon be out on Spotify? Im sooo excited about that! I will keep you updated and let you know when my first album is released. Meanwhile you can find all my songs on my YouTube channel, link in bio 😘

node.text:
The other week I uploaded a new video on my YouTube channel (link in bio) that I never shared here on Instagram since I traveled away the same day and forgot to share it here before I left 🙈
So I just wanted to give you a little glimpse of that video now, and if you want to see the whole video you can find the link in bio 😘
It contains a little bit of everything I've been up to in May and June. Also the whole building of my camper van, from start to finish. 

Hope you have a lovely summer so far! ❤ Take care everyone 🌻
